{
  "id": "019d2d88-8caa-7933-a7f0-efd15613b1e6",
  "content": "# Tiered Memory Architectures in AI Agent Systems (March 2026)\n\nThe field has converged on multi-tier memory as the dominant paradigm, drawing from CPU cache hierarchies and cognitive science.\n\n## Infrastructure Tiers (Hot/Warm/Cold)\n\n- **L1 Hot** (<1ms): In-memory or Redis-backed. Active conversation context, working memory, scratchpad. Redis reports 99% faster vector search (10ms vs 2s) vs disk.\n- **L2 Warm** (10-50ms): Vector database (Qdrant, Milvus, pgvector, Chroma). Recent sessions, extracted facts, entity summaries.\n- **L3 Cold** (100ms+): Persistent archival. Historical data, deprecated facts, audit trails.\n\nNVIDIA's ICMS platform (Rubin architecture, H2 2026) introduces hardware-level \"G3.5\" tier between GPU HBM and general storage via BlueField-4 DPUs — petabyte-scale flash-based context memory for KV cache reuse.\n\n## Cognitive Tiers (Tsinghua Survey, arxiv 2512.13564, Dec 2025)\n\n- **Working memory**: Current task state, active reasoning (Letta \"main context\" = RAM)\n- **Episodic memory**: Past actions, outcomes, task trajectories (Hindsight \"bank network\")\n- **Semantic/Factual memory**: World facts, entity relationships (Hindsight \"world network\")\n- **Procedural memory**: How to do things, skills, patterns (LangMem, Copilot Agent Skills)\n\n## Multi-Network Architecture (Hindsight — 91.4% LongMemEval, highest published)\n\nFour parallel networks: World (objective facts), Bank (first-person episodic), Opinion (subjective judgments with confidence), Observation (preference-neutral entity summaries). TEMPR runs all four retrieval channels in parallel with cross-encoder reranking.\n\n## MemOS (OS Abstraction, arxiv May 2025)\n\nThree layers: Parametric (model weights), Activation (inference state), Plaintext (external docs). MemCube abstraction enables tracking, fusion, and migration of heterogeneous memory across tasks.\n\n## MAGMA (arxiv 2601.03236, Jan 2026)\n\nRepresents each memory item across orthogonal semantic, temporal, causal, and entity graphs. Outperforms prior SOTA on both LoCoMo and LongMemEval while reducing retrieval latency.",
